- a striking contrast between

- as opposed to

Urbanization has significantly improved access to employment and education. In contrast, it has also intensified housing shortages and environmental pollution, which stand in sharp contrast to the relatively sustainable conditions found in rural areas.

- intensified
	Climate change has intensified extreme weather events.
	Urbanization has intensified traffic congestion.
	Public anxiety was intensified by economic uncertainty.
	Income inequality has been intensified by rapid economic growth.
	
	Housing shortages have intensified due to population growth.
	Deforestation has intensified environmental degradation.
	Air pollution has intensified as industrial activity expands.
	The urban heat island effect is intensified by dense construction.

	Competition in the job market has intensified over time.

- Exacerba


- Escalate
	Housing prices have escalated rapidly in urban areas.
	Poor urban planning has exacerbated housing shortages, aggravated traffic congestion, and escalated social tensions.